  <td class="diff-marker">−</td>
  <td class="diff-deletedline"><div>During this time of development, a person may become more preoccupied with feelings and thoughts of their individuality that are not easy to share with other individuals. This can be a result from feelings of shame, guilt, or alienation during childhood experiences.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite book |first1=Barbara M. |last1=Newman |first2=Philip R. |last2=Newman |year=2011 |chapter=Isolation |chapterurl=http://books.google.com/books?id=oTY_7osGmqUC&amp;pg=PA469 |page=469 |title=Development Through Life: A Psychosocial Approach |publisher=Wadsworth |isbn=978-1-111-34466-5}}&lt;/ref&gt;</div></td>
